## What this is and how it came to be:
The rapid adoption of Large Language Models (LLMs) in clinical and regulatory research has introduced significant risks regarding "hallucinations"
and the erosion of citation integrity. RAIL (ResinTox Augmented Intelligence Layer) is an application framework designed to enforce empirical traceability. 
By integrating a "tethered" storage architecture—allowing researchers to alternate between private local caches and synchronized cloud repositories — RAIL
can provide a verifiable Training Index for high-stakes intelligence gathering in fields such as toxicology, pharmacology, and regulatory science.

The RAIL-JS.html can be copied and pasted to run from any server, locally hosted web page or in an electron-app against a local or distributed llm-server of choice by entering a valid host. If you want to test against ResinTox RAIL-server and internal engine, that can be arranged - but setting up your own local server is highly recommended.

## IMPORTANT NOTE
The software, as is, is free to use for TESTING, REVIEW and further DEVELOPMENT. There are NO claims that this is a FULLY FUNCTIONING software that has been stress tested in different fields or in a large number of settings or situations at this time.

## Scientific Purpose & Scope
This repository serves as the official interactive **Proof of Concept (PoC)** and architectural simulator for the framework proposed in the paper: *"The Cognitive Exoskeleton: A Structured Pipeline for Augmented Intelligence in Scientific Formulation and Evidence Synthesis"* (Nilsson, 2026).

Rather than providing a production-ready Python backend, this client-side environment acts as a sandboxed **existence proof**. It visually and programmatically simulates how deterministic syntactic constraints, strict schema enforcement, and an Interactive Evidence Matrix can eliminate AI automation bias and prevent logical drift in high-stakes regulatory science.


